TERMS:
base class
derived class

ancestor class
parent class
child class
descendant class

LEGAL:
parentObject = childObject;
ancestorObject = descendantObject;

ILLEGAL;
childObject = parentObject;
descendantObject = ancestorObject;

ENGLISH NOTES:
Any time Any time an object of type parent is used, an object of type child or descendant can also be used. However, an ancestor object cannot be used in place of a parent object.
